how to make our special

01:41.401 --> 01:43.495
three-alarm colon cleaner.

01:45.272 --> 01:47.639
All right, guys. What do we do first?

01:47.741 --> 01:50.711
Well, first we've already browned up
a couple of pounds of meat.

01:50.777 --> 01:52.109
Now, we know you like beef.

01:52.178 --> 01:54.545
I love beef. Yeah. Oh, yeah.

01:54.614 --> 01:57.982
Well, we prefer rattlesnake. But today
we're going with Al's favorite...

01:58.051 --> 02:00.611
- Lean stewing turkey.
- That's right.

02:00.720 --> 02:02.058
Now, while that's simmering,
you want to add

02:02.088 --> 02:03.989
two cans of chopped, peeled tomatoes

02:04.090 --> 02:06.059
and a bottle of your favorite brew.

02:06.159 --> 02:07.731
And, of course,
there's always a debate about

02:07.761 --> 02:09.286
whether or not beans should be added.

02:09.395 --> 02:14.027
Actually, the debate begins two hours
after you've added the beans.

02:14.100 --> 02:15.605
That's right. What the hell?
We're men, right?

02:15.635 --> 02:17.126
Go for it, baby.

02:17.203 --> 02:19.138
Next you want to put in
your chili mix.

02:19.272 --> 02:22.401
Right. And a manly jalapeÃ±o pepper.

02:22.475 --> 02:25.240
Now, if there's women-folk partaking,
you might want to go easy.

02:25.312 --> 02:26.610
Oh, please!

02:28.081 --> 02:30.209
Now, you want to let this stew
for about a day.

02:30.283 --> 02:32.115
But we have a pot here
all ready for tasting.

02:32.185 --> 02:33.490
- All right, Heidi.
- That's great.

02:33.520 --> 02:34.681
Oh, yeah.

02:34.754 --> 02:38.191
Okay. Oh, clumsy me.

02:39.926 --> 02:43.419
- Okay, here you go, boys.
- Thank you.

02:44.531 --> 02:46.159
Oh, I'm sorry... "Men."

02:46.232 --> 02:50.169
Al! Al, not with a spoon. Always eat
three-alarm chili with a saltine.

02:50.236 --> 02:51.864
- Absolutely!
- That's right.

